    • Method Detail

      • getResult

        byte[] getResult()
        Get the transaction result. The result is obtained as part of the proposal endorsement so may be read immediately. It is not necessary to submit the transaction before getting the transaction result, but the transaction will not be committed to the ledger and its effects visible to other clients and transactions until after it has been submitted to the orderer.
        Returns:
        A transaction result.

      • getBytes

        byte[] getBytes()
        Get the serialized transaction message bytes.
        Returns:
        A serialized transaction.

      • getDigest

        byte[] getDigest()
        Get the digest of the serialized transaction. This is used to generate a digital signature.
        Returns:
        A hash of the transaction.

      • getTransactionId

        String getTransactionId()
        Get the transaction ID.
        Returns:
        A transaction ID.

      • submit

        byte[] submit()
       throws CommitException
        Submit the transaction to the orderer to be committed to the ledger. This method blocks until the transaction has been successfully committed to the ledger.
        Returns:
        A transaction result.
        Throws:
        CommitException - On commit failure.

      • submitAsync

        Supplier<TransactionPackage.TxValidationCode> submitAsync()
        Submit the transaction to the orderer to be committed to the ledger. This method returns immediately after the transaction is successfully delivered to the orderer. The returned Supplier may be used to subsequently wait for the transaction to be committed to the ledger.
        Returns:
        A commit handle.
